
[1]conoid

   CONOID, n. [Gr., a cone, form.]

   1. In geometry, a solid formed by the revolution of a conic section
   about its axis. If the conic section is a parabola, the resulting solid
   is a parabolic conoid, or paraboloid; if a hyperbola, the solid is a
   hyperbolic conoid, or hyperboloid; of an ellipse, an elliptic conoid, a
   spheroid, or an ellipsoid.

   2. In anatomy, a gland in the third ventricle of the brain, resembling
   a cone or pine-apple, and called the pineal gland.
